# LJI Obsidian second brain

**Vault path:** `C:\Users\zekes\Obsidian Vault\LJI Histology Project`

## On learning / explanation chats

When Zeke **states understanding** ("I learned…", "so that means…", "remember…", confirms a retain list):

1. Run **`lji-wiki-save`** workflow (see `.cursor/skills/lji-wiki-save/SKILL.md`).
2. File to the best matching note or `wiki/insights/`.
3. One-line confirm: `Saved to [[Note Title]]`.

Ask before saving only if the insight is ambiguous or contradicts an existing note.

## On questions about prior learning

When Zeke asks from memory, notes, or second brain ("what do I know about…", "from my Obsidian…", "what did I save…"):

1. Run **`lji-wiki-query`** (`.cursor/skills/lji-wiki-query/SKILL.md`).
2. Read `wiki/hot.md` → `wiki/index.md` → relevant pages.
3. Answer in **his saved framing**; cite `[[wikilinks]]`.
4. Use `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md` only for live repo status not in vault.

## Explicit commands

| Command | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `/save` | Save current answer (insight or synthesis) |
| `/save insight [title]` | New `wiki/insights/` note |
| `query quick: …` | hot + index only |

## Do not

- Skip vault read when Zeke references saved notes
- Overwrite insights without merging
- Store secrets or API keys in vault notes
